        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:29PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farley, or 28 miles southwest of Des Moines, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farley and Gladstone.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
